## Summary
On `openclaw@2026.4.15`, every agent turn against `anthropic/claude-opus-4-7` sends `thinking: {type: "enabled", budget_tokens: N}` on the first attempt. Anthropic rejects with `400 "thinking.type.enabled" is not supported for this model. Use "thinking.type.adaptive" and "output_config.effort"`. `pickFallbackThinkingLevel()` then retries with `thinking=off`, so users silently lose all extended thinking — even when `thinkingDefault: "xhigh"` is explicitly configured.

## Root cause
`supportsAdaptiveThinking()` in `dist/anthropic-vertex-stream-*.js` lists every 4.6 variant but omits 4.7:

```js
function supportsAdaptiveThinking(modelId) {
  return modelId.includes("opus-4-6") || modelId.includes("opus-4.6")
      || modelId.includes("sonnet-4-6") || modelId.includes("sonnet-4.6");
}
```

When the Anthropic adapter at the `createAnthropicTransportClient` call-site checks it for `claude-opus-4-7`, the check returns `false` and the adapter falls to the else branch:

```js
if (options?.thinkingEnabled) if (supportsAdaptiveThinking(model.id)) {
  params.thinking = { type: "adaptive" };
  if (options.effort) params.output_config = { effort: options.effort };
} else params.thinking = { type: "enabled", budget_tokens: ... };  // ← 4.7 hits this
```

There's a second place with the same omission: the OAuth/vertex transport-options builder (~line 6926 in my bundle):

```js
if (options?.reasoning) if (model.id.includes("opus-4-6") || model.id.includes("opus-4.6") || model.id.includes("sonnet-4-6") || model.id.includes("sonnet-4.6")) {
  opts.thinkingEnabled = true;
  opts.effort = { ..., xhigh: model.id.includes("opus-4-6") ... ? "max" : "high" }[options.reasoning] ?? "high";
} else { /* falls to budget_tokens path */ }
```

Both need `opus-4-7`. Additionally, `mapThinkingLevelToEffort`'s xhigh case currently returns `"high"` for 4.7 — per your own docs (https://docs.openclaw.ai/tools/thinking) xhigh on 4.7 should map to `output_config.effort: "xhigh"`, since Opus 4.7 adds an xhigh effort tier between `high` and `max`.

## Repro
```bash
# Fresh openclaw@2026.4.15, config with primary model claude-opus-4-7
openclaw agent --agent main --local --session-id repro-$(date +%s) --json -m "/think:xhigh hi" 2>&1 | grep -i "invalid_request\|unsupported"
# → "thinking.type.enabled" is not supported for this model...
# → unsupported thinking level for anthropic/claude-opus-4-7; retrying with off
```

## Suggested fix
Add `opus-4-7` and `opus-4.7` to:
1. `supportsAdaptiveThinking()`
2. The inline check in the vertex/oauth transport-options builder (the `model.id.includes(...)` chain at ~6926)
3. `mapThinkingLevelToEffort()` so 4.7 xhigh returns `"xhigh"` (not `"high"`) — matches your docs

I'm applying a local post-install patch for now; happy to send a PR if that helps. Related to #67710 (Opus 4.7 catalog fix) which shipped in 2026.4.15 but didn't touch the adapter.

## Environment
- OpenClaw `2026.4.15 (041266a)` (Homebrew Node global install)
- `anthropic/claude-opus-4-7` as primary via API key
- Fallbacks: opus-4-6, sonnet-4-6
- Config: `agents.defaults.thinkingDefault: "xhigh"`, also set on the main agent

### Bug type

Regression (worked before, now fails)

